content.description: This clean crack starts at OW/Chimney just left of Giu La Testa.  Easy climbing to either side or a hard direct start (10ish) gets to the biz, a lazor edged crack with tons of face holds make this a good trad lead for the grade.
content.location: Far left end of wall, just left of last bolted sport route on the left, Giu La Testa.

content.description: Follow bolts up to chain, shares last bolt and chains with The Hanging Tree.
content.location: Start in the black streak just right of The Hanging Tree.

content.description: Tuco would be proud.  Climb over bulge and up face past a bolt to a tree anchor.
content.protection: Although the placements are hard to find from the ground, this route protects well using thin, incipient cracks.  Pro is mostly thin nuts & microcams plus gear to a #1 camalot.
content.location: Start at bulge just left of The Hanging Tree.

climbs.name: Plain High Drifter
climbs.fa: M. Rangel, Mike S., Bret C.

content.description: The crack has thin pro and thin edges to start, this seemed cruxy to me.  The climbing was excellent and the pro adequate.
content.protection: Thin TCUs and nuts plus a couple cams to #3 Camalot
content.location: Walk 50yds to right of Angel Eyes, look for a 5' roof with a hand crack to its right; this route is next crack to right.  It climbs up to couple short roofs, goes up the center of final roof.

content.description: Climb up face and right-facing dihedral (crux down low) then follow easier crack to the top.  Crack at top is ~15' and easier, but not bolted; bring nuts for optional pro.  Bolted belay.
content.protection: Mostly sport, with optional nuts for easy 15' runout at top.
content.location: The bolted dihedral right of For a Few Ankles More

content.description: Look right at the overhang a few bolts up; going left is @ 10ish.
content.location: Furthest left bolted line on SWW.  At the large live oak at the base of the wall, go left @ 25' to the start at a ledge above the ground.

content.description: Getting past the lip of the roof is very difficult; a tcu could be placed in the crack if necessary to help you feel better about clipping the bolt past the lip. Cranking over the roof is easier if a foot jam overhead is used.
content.protection: all bolts plus one tcu maybe.
content.location: Look for the obvious roof with a crack in it.

content.description: Currently the route that is furthest right in the spag west area, past broken area/gully and to second 50 footish cliff. Route starts just right of small pine. Nice egdes, crux between 3rd and 4th bolt, move slightly right at 3rd bolt for a move or two to keep at grade.

climbs.name: Crack With No Name
climbs.fa: Mike S., Bret C., M. Rangel

content.description: Just 50 yds right of Angel Eyes is a 5' roof, immediately right of this is a hand crack behind a pine tree.  Climb on great face/crack to low-angle top out.
content.protection: Mostly hand-sized pro, nuts.  shares anchor with Dimensional Cowgirl.

content.description: In the center of the wall is a dihedral with a roof, start at the incipient crack and climb to top of dihedral, at it's end traverse left 5' to chains on For a Few Ankles More.
content.location: Located in center of routes, easily spotted by looking for the big roof just left.

content.description: Fun route, bit steeper than it looks with a fun bulgy move and good pro. Rock looks blocky but it's actually solid. A great warm up for the wall.
content.protection: Rack of singles .3 to #3 and nuts
content.location: Right of angel eyes is a chimney that splits the Spag Western Wall. Right of that chimney are two crack systems that top out at a tree. Bone Dry is just around the corner from those (Just right of "The Ugly"). It ascends an intermittent crack system just right of the prow/corner. At top step left for two bolt anchor.

content.description: Follow bolts past edges & slopers up a steep face, with crux at top.
content.location: Start at bolt line on steep face just left of the Angel Eyes crack, about 25' right of For a Few Ankles More.

content.description: Start just right of The Bad.  Follow a right-arching thin crack till it ends (#1 camalot), move up and left past a bolt, then straight up past more thin pro.
content.protection: Lots of very thin to a #1 camalot, 1 bolt.
content.location: Just right of The Bad and left of The Ugly's dirty offwidth.

content.description: A fun sport climb.  Start behind tree (tree is off!)and edge up & right, then straight up.
content.location: Start at the obvious tree on the left side of SWW, about 30' left of For a Few Ankles More.
